(84, 20, 0, '36', 'mat', 'Okay the \"present simple\" is the simple present tense. It is the tense you use when you want to talk about something that happens regularly. Example of simple present tense are: sing, sleep, dance, jump. He sings well. She dresses well. Sings and dresses are in simple present tense. Also, the past simple is the past tense of a verb. ', 1, 1, '2020-09-16 21:37:03'),
(85, 20, 0, '36', 'mat', 'Examples of the present tense and the past tense are: tell- told. Speak- spoke. Stand- stood.  Buy- bought. He bought a ball last week. Sarah sang yesterday. The word, bought and sang are past tense in the two sentences. That is all on the two tenses. If you still need more clarification, don\'t hesitate ( feel free) to ask questions.', 1, 1, '2020-09-16 21:48:30'),
