(48, 14, 'Classification of crystal', 1, '<p>Solids that have short-range order but lack long-range order are called&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.britannica.com/science/amorphous-solid\">amorphous</a>. Almost any material can be made&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/amorphous\">amorphous</a>&nbsp;by rapid solidification from the melt (molten state). This condition is unstable, and the solid will crystallize in time. If the timescale for crystallization is years, then the amorphous state appears stable. Glasses are an example of amorphous solids. In</p>\n', '{\"p120630889\":{\"instruction\":\"\",\"question\":\"what is physics\",\"type\":1,\"points\":1,\"imgs\":\"\",\"vids\":\"\",\"auds\":\"\",\"answer\":\"\",\"options\":\"d758893::::1::::::d27850::::2::::::d596344::::3::::::d101538::::49\",\"optionstype\":\"d758893::::0::::::d27850::::0::::::d596344::::0::::::d101538::::0\"},\"p92095994\":{\"instruction\":\"\",\"question\":[],\"type\":5,\"points\":1,\"imgs\":\"\",\"vids\":\"\",\"auds\":\"\",\"answer\":[],\"options\":\"\",\"optionstype\":\"\"}}', NULL, '{\"p120630889\":{},\"p92095994\":{}}', NULL, NULL, 0, '2020-10-28 12:26:05', 1, 1),
