(1, 1, '189', 'Heat Energy', 1, 1, 'At the end of the lesson students should be able to \nDefine heat\nState the effects of heat\nState the sources of heat energy', 'Heat energy, or thermal energy, is the energy of a substance or system in terms of the motion or vibration of its molecules. The faster the molecules in a substance move the more heat energy they have. ... Thermal physics encompasses thermodynamics, statistical mechanics, and kinetic theory.', 5, '2020-08-16 03:47:00', '2020-10-30 03:47:00', 0, 0, '2020-08-24 02:47:40'),
